XLDB 2017-=20
10th Extremely Large Databases Conference (https://xldb2017.uca.fr =
<https://xldb2017.uca.fr/>)

October 10th-12th, Clermont-Ferrand, France

2nd and last Call for Lightning Talks and Posters
------------------------------------------------

XLDB events are uniquely targeted gatherings that discuss the real-world =
challenges, practical considerations, and nuts-and-bolts solutions in =
the realm of managing and analyzing extreme scale data sets. Attendees =
include Big Data users from industry and science, government, =
developers, researchers, and providers.

XLDB 2017 will feature lightning talks (allocated five-minute per talk =
presented sequentially without interruption). There will be two =
lightning talk sessions, one per day, each of which will be followed by =
a 90-minutes poster session. Speakers are welcome (but not required) to =
prepare a poster. Speakers will be expected to attend the poster session =
to answer follow-up questions regardless.

If you are interested in giving a lightning talk, you should submit an =
abstract with less than 500 words (1 page in pdf format) at:  =
https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=3Dxldb2017 =
<https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=3Dxldb2017>


Submission deadline for the 2nd call is September 10, 2017.


Poster-only submissions are also welcome.

Please note we will only consider non-sales talks/posters, highly =
relevant to managing and analyzing extremely large data sets.

The talks will be selected by the XLDB-2017 scientific committee.

Lightning talk speakers and poster presenters are required to register =
for the conference (e.g., the registration fee is not waived).
--=20
